  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Black Fish Foundation will use the grant funds to support its recently launched Citizen Inspector Network. The Network is aimed at creating a community led network of citizen fisheries inspectors to monitor suspected illegal, unregulated, and unreported (IUU) fishing in Europe. The Network will empower citizens and build a community to encourage citizens to be actively involved in fisheries enforcement and to engage citizens in the broader movement for marine conservation. Citizen inspectors will help to coordinate and share information with the media and other NGOs. The wider aim is for this program to be replicated in other regions and further engage citizens in the enforcement of fisheries regulations and the protection of their local marine environment.</narrative>
  </description>
